Authors: 
Enrico Bozzetto, Simone Sticca, Daniele Spalazzi

Description:
This project allow to test matrix multiplication with systolica array architecture using MPI.

Requirements:
openmpi
gcc compiler
SLURM job scheduler

Project structure:
csv/
results/
logs/
csvutils.c
matrixUtils.h
calculateReference.c
checkResults.c
initializeMatrices.c
systolicMultiplication.c
submitReferenceMatrix.sh
submitExperiment.sh
submitExperiment2Nodes.sh
submitExperimentMultipleNodes.sh
referenceMatrix.slurm
systolicRun.slurm
systolicRunMultipleNodes.slurm


Usage:
To run experiments is needed firstly to create the input and reference matrices with submitReferenceMatrix.sh script.
Run: submitReferenceMatrix.sh <DIM1> [DIM2 ...]
Output: input matrices and reference matrices for each dimension and for the 10 repetitions are saved in csv/ folder the execution results for reference value are saved in results/reference_${DIM}.csv.

Then different experiments can be run using the same matrices dimensions.

1. Single node experiment
Run: submitExperiment.sh <NUM_DIMS> <DIM1> [DIM2 ...] <PROC1> [PROC2 ...]
Output: execution results for systolic array multiplication are saved in results/systolic_${DIM}_${PROCS}_${REP}.csv and matrices are saved in csv/ folder.

2. Two nodes experiment
Run: submitExperiment2Nodes.sh <NUM_DIMS> <DIM1> [DIM2 ...] <PROC1> [PROC2 ...]
Output: execution results for systolic array multiplication are saved in results/multi_nodes_systolic_${DIM}_${PROCS}_${REP}.csv and matrices are saved in csv/ folder.


To merge the results in single csv file for each experiment type use merge.sh script.
Run: merge.sh